            . I belong to the Hope. The prisoner came on board on the 30th of November; he staid from twelve o'clock till a quarter after ten at night - he came to see the ship's company generally; I had seen the watch hanging up on the sky-light bolt - when he was gone I missed it; I believe one of the ship's boys put him on shore.</p>
